&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Several
days ago your letter came, revealing your struggles with sexual identity
disorder and what you have proposed to do about the matter. You will not be
surprised, I am sure, to find a concerned ear for you in the situation you are handling,
but you will not find a sympathetic ear for what you are contemplating doing
with it. There is a distinction between the disorder itself and what a person
proposes to do with it. The disorder may be understandable; what people decide
to do with it is another matter.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>CHRISTIANS AND TEMPORAL AUTHORITIES</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/ethics/christians-and-temporal-authorities/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/ethics/christians-and-temporal-authorities/</guid><description>&lt;style>
