between people do exist, but they do not normally deal with matters that
impinge on ethical considerations. Supposing the continuity of human nature as
the background for the Golden Rule is preferable to supposing that the Golden
Rule describes a non-content procedure, the approach of R. M. McIver, “The Deep
Beauty of the Golden Rule” in &lt;i>Philosophy and Contemporary Issues&lt;/i>, pp.
233-39.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>ETHICS STANDARDS</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/ethics/ethics-standards/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/ethics/ethics-standards/</guid><description>&lt;style>
