sensible because (a) incompatible moral beliefs and practices exist, and (b) no
one seems able to establish a universal basis for ethical theory.  &lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>SOME VALUES OF LOVE AS AN ETHICAL PRINCIPLE</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/ethics/some-values-of-love-as-an-ethical-principle/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/ethics/some-values-of-love-as-an-ethical-principle/</guid><description>&lt;style>
