&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:justify'>&lt;span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>            Love gets us past legal minimums of do’s
and don’t’s. It provides a basis for going beyond the call of duty, takes into
consideration other people’s differing preferences, watches out for negative
effects on weaker brothers’ behavior, and concerns itself with good and better,
not just with good and bad. Love fosters a concern for enhancing the quality of
other people’s lives, not just with the rightness or wrongness of specific
behaviors relative to some standard.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>STRAY NOTATIONS ON THE COMPLEXITY OF ETHICAL BEHAVIOR</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/ethics/stray-notations-on-the-complexity-of-ethical-behavior/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/ethics/stray-notations-on-the-complexity-of-ethical-behavior/</guid><description>&lt;style>
